# EmailJS Configuration
# Get these values from https://www.emailjs.com/dashboard/admin

# Your EmailJS Public Key (found in Account > API Keys)
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here

# Your EmailJS Service ID (the email service you connected, e.g., Gmail, Outlook)
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_your_service_id

# Your EmailJS Template ID (the email template you created)
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_your_template_id

# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Go to https://www.emailjs.com and sign up (free)
# 2. Go to Account > API Keys and copy your Public Key
# 3. Go to Email Services and add an email service (Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo, etc.)
#    - For Gmail: Use "Gmail" service and authorize EmailJS
# 4. Go to Email Templates and create a new template with these variables:
#    - {{to_email}} - recipient email
#    - {{client_name}} - client name
#    - {{invoice_number}} - invoice number
#    - {{amount}} - invoice amount
#    - {{due_date}} - due date
#    - {{issue_date}} - issue date
#    - {{business_name}} - your business name
#    - {{project_name}} - project name
#    - Other variables you want to include
# 5. Copy your Service ID and Template ID
# 6. Create a .env file (same as this file but without .example)
# 7. Add your values to the .env file
# 8. Restart your dev server: npm start

# TEMPLATE EXAMPLE HTML:
# <h2>Invoice {{invoice_number}}</h2>
# <p>Dear {{client_name}},</p>
# <p>Please find your invoice below:</p>
# <ul>
#   <li>Amount: ${{amount}}</li>
#   <li>Project: {{project_name}}</li>
#   <li>Issue Date: {{issue_date}}</li>
#   <li>Due Date: {{due_date}}</li>
# </ul>
# <p>Thank you for your business!</p>
